📘 Legal Virtual Lawyer – India

AI-powered legal assistant using BNS, BNSS, and BSA as the knowledge base
Tech Stack: Python · FastAPI · Qdrant · RAG · Local/NVIDIA/OpenAI embeddings · PyMuPDF · VS Code + GitHub Copilot

📌 Project Overview

This project aims to build a Legal Virtual Lawyer for Indian law that can:

Answer legal questions using authentic statutory content

Retrieve and cite relevant sections from:

Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita (BNS)

Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita (BNSS)

Bharatiya Sakshya Adhiniyam (BSA)

Provide structured guidance, explanations, and legal options

Use a legal-agent workflow that activates when the user explicitly asks for “legal advice”

Follow safety rules (no hallucinations, citations only from retrieved sections, disclaimers, etc.)

This is not a fully-fledged lawyer, but a high-quality legal information and guidance system backed by RAG, embeddings, and LLM reasoning.

🏗️ Project Architecture
1. Knowledge Ingestion Layer

Input: Official PDFs of BNS, BNSS, BSA

Extraction using PyMuPDF

Section detection via regex

Clean, structured chunks with:

act

section

heading

chunk text

source pages

Embedding generation:

Local (sentence-transformers)

or OpenAI embeddings

Storage in Qdrant Vector DB

Script implemented:

scripts/ingest_pdfs.py

2. Retrieval Layer (RAG)

User query → embed → similarity search in Qdrant

Retrieve top-k statute chunks

Passed to LLM for grounded reasoning

Model must answer only using retrieved evidence

Citations shown with section numbers + page references

3. LLM Reasoning Layer

Two modes:

A) Assistant Mode

For factual Q&A:

“What does Section 120 of BNS say?”

“What is the difference between FIR and complaint?”

Uses RAG only

Must cite sections used

B) Legal-Agent Mode

Triggered when user asks:

“What should I do?”

“Give me legal advice”

“I am accused of ___, what next?”

Agent performs:

Intent detection

Consent screen

Collect facts (who, what, when, where)

Retrieve statutory evidence

Multi-step chain:

Identify legal issues

Map relevant sections

Options + pros/cons

Recommended next steps

Risk flags (immediate danger or criminal liability)

Output structured JSON

4. Application Layer (FastAPI)

(Not built yet — upcoming)

Endpoints:

/query — RAG + assistant mode

/advice — activates legal agent

/sections/{act}/{section} — direct statute lookup

/health — service health

5. UI Layer (Streamlit/React)

(Not built yet — upcoming)

Features:

Chat interface

Mode indicators (assistant vs agent)

Consent panels

Evidence viewer (PDF citation highlighting)

Exportable chat transcript

